    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;Babel is a loop-avoiding, distance-vector routing protocol that is robust and efficient both in ordinary wired networks and in wireless mesh networks.  This document describes the Babel routing protocol and obsoletes RFC 6126 and RFC 7557.&lt;/p&gt;</t>
